data.enText: We pushed our way through the throng.
to go somewhere or be present somewhere in large numbers
The children thronged into the hall.

data.chText: 人们成群结队地去看他的新戏。
data.enText: People are thronging to see his new play.
to be full of people, cars, etc.

data.chText: 小餐馆里都挤满了学生。
data.enText: The cafes were thronging with students.
The streets were thronged with people.
to be full of people, cars, etc.

data.chText: 小餐馆里都挤满了学生。
data.enText: The cafes were thronging with students.
The streets were thronged with people.

value.def: A throng is a large crowd of people.

example.ex: An official pushed through the throng.
example.tran: 一名官员费力地挤过人群。

value.def: When people throng somewhere, they go there in great numbers.

example.ex: The crowds thronged into the mall.
...the multitudes that throng around the Pope.
example.tran: 拥在教皇周围的教众甚多

value.def: If people throng a place, they are present there in great numbers.

example.ex: They throng the beaches between late June and early August.
example.tran: 6 月底到 8 月初，他们群聚在海滩上。

example.ex: The streets are thronged with people.
